-content_for :navbar do
  %li.nav-item
    %a.nav-link{:href => "#about"} About
  %li.nav-item
    %a.nav-link{:href => "#support"} Support Us

-content_for :alert do
  %div.alert.alert-warning
    %p
      IMPORTANT NOTICE: PumpSpot is a new FOSS project, just trying to get off the ground. We need your help. The site is currently lacking (severely) in data and we need community efforts to populate the database. A document will drafted soon to outline a proper process to submit records to the database. For now a pull request on Github is the way to go.

%header.bg-primary.bg-gradient.text-white
  .container.px-4.text-center
    %h1.fw-bolder PumpSpot
    %p.lead Open database of nearby tappable water resources.
    %a.btn.btn-lg.btn-light{:href => "/map"} View Map

%section#about
  .container.px-4
    .row.gx-4.justify-content-center
      .col-lg-8
        %h2 About this Site
        %p.lead PumpSpot provides a map marked with the locations of over /insert number here/ tappable water resources.
        %ul
          %li Click the button above to open the map
%section#support
  .container.px-4
    .row.gx-4.justify-content-center
      .col-lg-8
        %h2 Support The Project
        %p.lead Here are some various ways to support the project.
        %ul
          %li
            %a{href: "https://github.com/joshburnsxyz/pumpspot"} Contribute |
            to the project on Github
          %li
            %a{href: "mailto:joshyburnss@gmail.com"} Email me |
            with submissions to the database, or contribute directly with a
            PR on Github.
